{"key":"processedPost-10054651","value":{"id":10054651,"first":10053902,"last":10065557,"when":1238190710,"utime":"03/28/09 12:51 AM","content":"To add to the above, perhaps you're overloading.&nbsp; Make sure when you load the jars, there is space around each one.&nbsp; The glass expands slightly as it heats and if the jars are jammed in tight, they'll break.&nbsp; It's better to use two or three rows stacked on top of each other than for them to be jammed in tightly side to side.<br /><br />As said above already, make sure you have holes in the lids, the jars are elevated out of the water on a trivet or jar lid rings, and don't touch the PC until after it cools enough to touch without gloves.&nbsp; NEVER lift the weight to let pressure out.<br />RR","title":"Re: I'm having serious problems with cracked jars"}}